{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17491621","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17491621"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T05:55:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T05:55:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1000"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1000","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1000"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.21,0.5,0.08,0.17,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1000"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42792"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1000","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1000"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1000"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27753"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"28"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"461"},{"type":"tags","id":"1094"},{"type":"tags","id":"1151"},{"type":"tags","id":"2597"},{"type":"tags","id":"3374"},{"type":"tags","id":"3456"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"8116"},{"type":"tags","id":"9060"},{"type":"tags","id":"9598"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"4894"},{"type":"contributions","id":"4895"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42792","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/42792"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 80-year-old woman is being assessed for management of a recently diagnosed carcinoma of the oesophagus, following presentation for a four-month history of dysphagia and 10kg weight loss. She has a medical history of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, with recurrent exacerbations despite medical management and NYHA stage III heart failure. On examination, she looks cachectic, but there are no specific abnormalities to be found. The endoscopy found a 5 cm long stenotic tumour in the lower oesophagus, which was confirmed as a squamous cell carcinoma. CT and PET staging showed a locally advanced tumour (T4) with no evidence of distant metastases (M0).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Non-invasive comfort measures only","Endoscopic oesophageal stent","Chemotherapy","Radiotherapy","Total parenteral nutrition"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EGiven this woman has a locally advanced tumour (T4) and has serious co-morbidities, a palliative approach is more appropriate than a curative one. A \u003Cstrong\u003Estent\u003C/strong\u003E is likely to give good relief of her dysphagia, provided she is able to keep to a soft diet. This approach should have a significant positive impact on her quality of life, despite not being a curative treatment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENon-invasive comfort measures\u003C/strong\u003E may be considered after discussion with the patient and her family, however given the expected symptomatic benefit from stenting this is likely to yield a better quality of life for the patient.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EChemotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E may be considered if a curative approach were to be attempted, including being used in conjunction with surgical resection and/or radiotherapy. However, it is likely that chemotherapy alone will decrease the patient\u2019s quality of life with a relatively low chance of cure. \u003Cstrong\u003ERadiotherapy\u003C/strong\u003E would likely worsen her respiratory problems.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETotal parental nutrition\u003C/strong\u003E is typically not a good long-term nutrition option due to a significant risk of bacteraemia and other complications. More suitable options in patients with untreatable dysphagia may include a nasogastric tube or percutaneous endoscopic gastrostomy.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["A mesh stent provides good palliation for patients with untreatable oesophageal cancer and severe dysphagia."],"references":["Shah MA, Kennedy EB, Catenacci DV, Deighton DC, Goodman KA, Malhotra NK, et al. Treatment of Locally Advanced Esophageal Carcinoma: ASCO Guideline. J Clin Oncol. 2020;38(23):2677-2694. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32568633/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27753"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1000"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"27753","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/27753"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-02-19T10:37:17+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-02-19T10:37:17+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1000"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"42792"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"28","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/28"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc95","name":"Palliative Care","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":